# Voting Analysis Unified - Specstory

## Project Overview
A comprehensive web application hub analyzing elections and ballot measures across multiple jurisdictions:
- California Proposition 50 (Congressional Redistricting)
- King County, Washington Proposition 1 (AFIS Funding)
- Larimer County, Colorado (Transportation & Elections)

## Repository Structure
- `index.html` - Main hub page
- `prop50.html` - California Proposition 50 analysis
- `king-county.html` - King County analysis
- `larimer-county.html` - Larimer County analysis
- `styles.css` - Unified styling
- `app.js` - Application logic
- `data.js` - District and election data
- `deploy.sh` - Quick deployment script
- `timestamp.json` - Auto-generated timestamp file

## Features
- Interactive visualizations with Chart.js
- Comprehensive source citations
- Responsive design
- Auto-updating timestamps
- Multi-timezone support (PST/MST)
- Auto-refresh functionality

## Deployment
- Hosted on GitHub Pages: https://bobbyinfj.github.io/voting-analysis-unified/
- Auto-deploys on push to main branch
- Uses `./deploy.sh` script for quick updates

## Data Sources
All data compiled from publicly available sources including:
- Official government websites
- News organizations
- Academic research
- Interactive mapping tools

